snippet.textDisplay: Well, I gotta say, that part about it being in a remote location isn’t necessarily true. I’ve driven by the prison complex quite a few times actually. Florence is a full on town that just so happens to have the world’s most secure prison in it. A veterans nursing home is only about 3 minutes of driving away, there’s a Super 8 motel in very close proximity to the complex, and the town of Florence is actually very close by. Barely a 15 minute drive away from that is Cañon City. Aside from that, this video is spot on.

snippet.textDisplay:
There's one way out...which I am basically modifying from my favorite book, Count of Monte Cristo.

If somehow you got ahold of a medicine that slowed down your heart rate and/or paid off a medical examiner you could fake your death and end up having your body moved to a funeral home and then shipped home.  

That or pay off a few guards who will find you and move the body, the examiner to sign the death warrant, the funeral home to ship the body, and then deliver the "body" to Mexico.
